  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study was (1) to investigate changes in gait, balance, fine motor
      function, and muscle tone, and (2) to find out if there is a correlation between muscle
      tone/presence of paratonia and motor function (gross and fine) in mild and moderate
      dementia.Three groups of participants were included in the study: healthy elderly (n=60),
      participants with mild dementia (n=31) and participants with moderate dementia (n=31).
      Measurements of fine motor function, balance, gait, presence of paratonia and muscle tone
      measurements were performed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
